	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=169081><span id= >Lotorr</span></a><br><span id=notbold>9 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Damage Bonus works like this:<br><br>Say you hit a mob with this weapon. Lets say your initial hit was for 60 damage. The damage Bonus on this weapon (45) is added to the total, so you would actually hit for 105 dmg on your poke. Damage Bonus does not add to the base damage of the weapon (Meaning it does not make the tusk an 85/44 weapon). The Cold Dmg IS added to the tusk's base damage (making weapon 44/44 ASSUMING that the monster fails its' cold resistance check).</p>&nbsp;<br>Lotorr Trueheart<br>Half Elf Druid</td></td></tr>
